    • Field Detail

      • id

        private int id
        id

      • gender

        private java.lang.String gender
        gender - Normally set to "m" or "f". (Can be set to "x" if Other genders are enabled). If there is missing data the default value of null is set.

      • ageRangeCode

        private int ageRangeCode
        ageRangeCode (0 = 0-9, 10 = 10-19, 20 = 20-29, 30 = 30-39 etc - 90 is the maximum for those older than 90). If there is missing data the default value of 1000 is set.

      • lastOrderedProducts

        private java.lang.String lastOrderedProducts
        last ordered productsIds - a colon-separated list of the most-recently ordered products with productId and timestamp separated by a space (eg. ":2 2018-07-03:41 1525795475027:33 2018-06-23:42 1525795476027:" - these will be the most-recent 10 or fewer different products ordered). The timestamp is the number of milliseconds since 1st January 1970.

      • lastViewedProducts

        private java.lang.String lastViewedProducts
        last viewed productsIds . A list of productId and timestamp pairs that records the last viewed products identified by the specified productsIds. This data is recorded in the customer tag PRODUCTS_TIME_VIEWED. It's a colon-separated list of the most-recently viewed products with productId and timestamp separated by a space (eg. ":2 2018-07-03:41 1525795475027:33 2018-06-23:42 1525795476027:" - these will be the most-recent 10 or fewer different products viewed). The timestamp is the number of milliseconds since 1st January 1970.

      • wishlistProducts

        private java.lang.String wishlistProducts
        Wish list products. A list of productId and timestamp pairs that records the products in the customer's wishlist and the timestamp the items were saved to the wish list. The products are identified by the specified productsIds. This data is recorded in the customer tag PRODUCTS_TIME_IN_WISHLIST. It's a colon-separated list of the most-recently added products with productId and timestamp separated by a space (eg. ":2 2018-07-03:41 1525795475027:33 2018-06-23:42 1525795476027:" - these will be the most-recent 10 or fewer different products added). The timestamp is the number of milliseconds since 1st January 1970.

      • basketProducts

        private java.lang.String basketProducts
        Basket products. A list of productId and timestamp pairs that records the products in the customer's shopping basket/cart and the timestamp the items were saved to the basket. The products are identified by the specified productsIds. This data is recorded in the customer tag PRODUCTS_TIME_IN_CART. It's a colon-separated list of the most-recently added products with productId and timestamp separated by a space (eg. ":2 2018-07-03:41 1525795475027:33 2018-06-23:42 1525795476027:" - these will be the most-recent 10 or fewer different products added). The timestamp is the number of milliseconds since 1st January 1970.

      • numberOfLogons

        private int numberOfLogons
        numberOfLogons

      • type

        private int type
        Type of customer. Only these two types will be exported:
        • CustomerMgr.CUST_TYPE_REGISTERED_CUST = 0 = Registered customer
        • CustomerMgr.CUST_TYPE_NON_REGISTERED_CUST = 2 = Non-Registered customer (Guest)

      • accountCreatedMs

        private long accountCreatedMs
        accountCreatedMs. A timestamp representing the date/time that the account was created. It is the number of milliseconds since 1st January 1970 (Epoch timestamp).

      • newsletter

        private java.lang.String newsletter
        newsletter. "1" = Customer is subscribed to the newsletter or "0" = Customer is not subscribed to the newsletter.

      • productNotifications

        private java.lang.String productNotifications
        productNotifications. a colon-separated string of productId and timestamp pairs for products that the customer has requested update notifications on and the date that notification was set up. The timestamp is the number of milliseconds since 1st January 1970.

      • addressCity

        private java.lang.String addressCity
        addressCity. Customer's default address - City. If there is missing data the default value of null is set.

      • addressPostcode

        private java.lang.String addressPostcode
        addressCity. Customer's default address - Postcode. If there is missing data the default value of null is set.

      • addressState

        private java.lang.String addressState
        addressState. Customer's default address - State. If there is missing data the default value of null is set.

      • addressCountry

        private java.lang.String addressCountry
        addressCity. Customer's default address - Country. If there is missing data the default value of null is set.

      • custom1

        private java.lang.String custom1
        custom1. Custom field for the customer. Depending on the mapping it could be from a Customer custom field or from a customer's tag value. If null no tag is output.

      • custom2

        private java.lang.String custom2
        custom2. Custom field for the customer. Depending on the mapping it could be from a Customer custom field or from a customer's tag value. If null no tag is output.

      • custom3

        private java.lang.String custom3
        custom3. Custom field for the customer. Depending on the mapping it could be from a Customer custom field or from a customer's tag value. If null no tag is output.

      • custom4

        private java.lang.String custom4
        custom4. Custom field for the customer. Depending on the mapping it could be from a Customer custom field or from a customer's tag value. If null no tag is output.

      • custom5

        private java.lang.String custom5
        custom5. Custom field for the customer. Depending on the mapping it could be from a Customer custom field or from a customer's tag value. If null no tag is output.

      • dummyTimeStamp

        private final java.lang.String dummyTimeStamp
        Use this as a dummy timestamp if we don't have a real timestamp
